    <text id="B0688T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Waldo notifies a Miss E. James, a teacher in Harrisonburg, that he is sending her
                    the articles she requested.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">RF&amp;AL</abbr>
                    4th <abbr expan="Division">Div.</abbr> 9 <abbr expan="Sub-District">Sub
                        Dist</abbr><lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Miss E. James<lb/>Harrisonburg, <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-10-20"><abbr expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 20, 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p> Your letter of the 17<unclear>
                        <hi rend="super">th</hi>
                        <abbr expan="instant">inst.</abbr>
                    </unclear> is received - The articles referred to <unclear>therein
                    have</unclear> been received and receipted for by me <unclear>as in</unclear>
                    good condition, &amp; have made arrangements with Mr. Stanley of this place
                    to transfer them to Harrisonburg by wagon arriving in that place probably
                    sometime tomorrow or next day. The expense of transportation from this place to
                    Harrisonburg will be $2<hi rend="super">
                        <hi rend="underline">00</hi>
                    </hi></p>

                <p>Have not heard from Mr. Scott. <abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr> McDonnell of
                    Winchester <unclear>wrote me</unclear> today that Mr. Brackett <abbr
                        expan="Superintendent">Supt</abbr> of Schools in the Valley would perhaps
                    send teachers if more had already arrived.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="obedient servant">ob
                        Servt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>Roswell Waldo<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">ASA
                            Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
